  "body": "This PR adds the `React.createRef()` API â€“ which can be thought of as a replacement for those who use string refs or for those who don't need the powerful features from callback refs. To find out more about this new API, see its respective RFC:  https://github.com/reactjs/rfcs/pull/17.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nclass MyComponent extends React.Component {\r\n  divRef = React.createRef();\r\n\r\n  render() {\r\n    return <div><input type=\"text\" ref={this.divRef} /></div>;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  componentDidMount() {\r\n    this.divRef.current.focus();\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```",
